comments: Goodwin (CLE) brings his hands forward toward Bagley III (DET) and marginal contact occurs to Bagley III's front as he dribbles in transition.
Okoro (CLE) brushes Cunningham's (DET) left arm and marginal contact occurs after Cunningham receives the pass.
Markkanen (CLE) and Stewart (DET) come together at the same spot in the lane and incidental foot-to-foot contact occurs.
Mobley (CLE) touches the ball last before it goes out of bounds.
Markkanen (CLE) brings his right forearm toward Joseph's (DET) side and marginal contact occurs after Joseph's gather. Mobley (CLE) then cleanly blocks the driving shot attempt.
Joseph (DET) is moving alongside Goodwin's (CLE) path when marginal body contact occurs during Goodwin's drive into the lane.
Stewart (DET) establishes himself in a screening position in Okoro's (CLE) path and absorbs the contact to his upper body before marginal leg-to-leg contact occurs.
Bey (DET) is moving forward when marginal body contact occurs with Mobley (CLE) as Mobley is pivoting.
Stewart (DET) initiates contact with Markkanen's (CLE) right arm and affects his dunk attempt.
Okoro (CLE) is moving alongside Cunningham's (DET) path and is retreating away from Cunningham, who moves toward Okoro to initiate the marginal body contact.
Bey (DET) and Markkanen (CLE) engage and disengage with one another as they move under the screen.
Allen (CLE) firms up in his screening position in Bey's (DET) path and absorbs the contact as Bey goes under.
Grant (DET) is bracing for the impending body contact and absorbs it as it occurs with Allen (CLE) as they each attempt to maintain post position.
Allen (CLE) gathers the ball on his left foot and establishes his right foot as his pivot. He legally lifts his pivot foot to shoot the ball and does so before his pivot foot returns to the floor.
Grant (DET) backs away from Allen (CLE) and marginal contact occurs with Allen's left side as Allen is losing his balance during his upward shooting motion.
Mobley (CLE) delivers contact to Cunningham's (DET) back after Cunningham retrieves the rebound.
Bey (DET) and Markkanen (CLE) engage and disengage with one another during the inbound.
Bey (DET) and Allen (CLE) engage and disengage with one another during rebounding.
Joseph (DET) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Allen (CLE) before incidental arm contact occurs during rebounding.
Following the dislodge, Joseph (DET) is already losing his balance prior to marginal contact being made by Allen (CLE) to Joseph's upper half as they each pursue the loose ball.
Allen (CLE) brings his hands toward Stewart's (DET) back as Stewart backs up toward him and marginal contact occurs as Allen releases away to pursue the long rebound.
Markkanen (CLE) cleanly back-taps the ball toward the perimeter before any incidental contact occurs with Bey (DET) or Joseph (DET) during rebounding.
Mobley (CLE) establishes himself in a screening position in Grant's (DET) path and absorbs the contact.
Stewart (DET) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he is imminently actively guarding Allen (CLE).
Bey (DET) and Markkanen (CLE) engage and disengage with one another off-ball.
Grant (DET) attempts to commit a take foul on Mobley (CLE) and the contact is marginal.
Cunningham (DET) initiates contact across Allen's (CLE) right arm and affects the put-back attempt.
